SECTION 5.
.
Designated Engineer in the State of Washington
 
5.1 The Board of Directors, as required by the Revised Code of Washington, has appointed a licensed professional engineer in the State of Washington the Designated Engineer as being in responsible charge for the practice of engineering performed by the Corporation in Washington.
.
Appointment of Designated Engineer
 
5.2 The Board of Directors grants and delegates to the Designated Engineer the full authority to make all final engineering decisions on behalf of the Corporation with respect to engineering work performed in the State of Washington.
.
Grant of Authority to the Designated Engineer
 
5.3 The Board of Directors grants and delegates to the appropriate officers of the Corporation the authority to designate each successor Designated Engineer as being in responsible charge for the practice of engineering and to notify the Washington Board of Registration for Professional Engineers and Land Surveyors of the appointment of each successor Designated Engineer within 30 days after the effective date of the appointment.
