Item 2.01               Completion of Acquisition or Disposition of Assets
On September 20, 2006, The Boeing Company, a Delaware corporation ("Boeing") completed its acquisition of Aviall Inc., a Delaware corporation ("Aviall") pursuant to an agreement and plan of merger, dated as of April 30, 2006 among Boeing, Boeing Avenger, Inc., a Delaware corporation and a direct wholly owned subsidiary of Boeing, and Aviall.  Boeing purchased Aviall for $48 per share or $1.7 billion, plus the assumption of debt, net of cash existing on Aviall's balance sheet, of $448 million.  Aviall will report to Boeing Commercial Aviation Services and operate as a wholly owned subsidiary.
A press release announcing the completion of the purchase of Aviall is attached hereto and is incorporated herein by reference.
