. A Participant's Interest Credit Account shall be credited monthly with interest on all amounts in that account during the preceding month. Interest will be computed during each calendar year at the mean between the high and the low during the first eleven months of the preceding year of yields on Aa-rated Industrial Bonds as reported by Moody's Investors Service, Inc., rounded to the nearest 1/4th of one percent. The Company will notify Participants annually of the established interest rate and the status of their respective Interest Credit Accounts.
