property, plant and equipment additions
Increase in Adjusted Earnings Per Share
Adjusted earnings per share is defined as GAAP adjusted for certain significant charges or credits. Management believes the increase in adjusted earnings per share is important to understanding the company's on-going operations and provide additional insights into underlying business performance. Significant charges or credits are described in the attachments to this release which provide reconciliations between GAAP earnings per share and adjusted earnings per share.
